The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Cheating cost: $492,400
                                                                                                               Cheating cost: $492,400
                            
	London, Aug. 18 (Reuters): Never again honey  and heres a diamond to say sorry.        
	Every time British businessman Robert Charlton cheated on his wife, he bought her some extravagant jewellery to try to make amends. After 26 years of marriage, Elizabeth Charlton had more than 40 glittering pieces.        
	Charltons infidelity cost him nearly $492,400 it emerged last month, when his daughter auctioned off the late couples jewellery collection. Charlton, who died in 1974, bought his wife antique diamond earrings, bracelets and rings.                                                                                                                                                                             
